%e A391905 a(1) = 49 because {12, 24, 41, 49} is a primitive Pythagorean quadruple, and subset {12, 24, 41} is also a subset of primitive Pythagorean quadruple {12, 24, 31, 41}.
%o A391905 (PARI) is_a391905(h)={for(x=1, sqrtint(h^2/3), for(y=x, sqrtint((h^2-x^2)/2), if(!issquare(h^2-x^2-y^2), next); my(z=sqrtint(h^2-x^2-y^2)); if(gcd([h, x, y, z])!=1 || !issquare(z^2-y^2-x^2), next); my(w=sqrtint(z^2-y^2-x^2)); if(gcd([w, x, y, z])==1, return(1)))); 0}
